    "body": "### Problem\r\n\r\n8ba73f0e4cc6 deprecated `vim.diagnostic.goto_next` in favor of `vim.diagnostic.jump`, and reimplements `goto_next` in terms of `jump`.  This is fine.  However, when reimplementing `goto_next`, we forgot that the default behavior of `goto_next` is to show a floating window with the error (the `float` option).\r\n\r\nWe should update `goto_next`'s implementation to call `jump` with `float=true`.\r\n\r\n### Steps to reproduce using \"nvim -u minimal_init.lua\"\r\n\r\n1. use neovim 0.10\r\n2. open file with LSP errors\r\n3. run `:lua vim.diagnostic.goto_next()`\r\n4. note that you visit the next diag and a float opens with the error\r\n5. switch to neovim> 8ba73f0e4cc6\r\n6. repeat steps 2-3\r\n\r\n### Expected behavior\r\n\r\nExpected: Should open float with the error.\r\n\r\nActual: Doesn't open float.\r\n\r\nI suggest two changes:\r\n1. We should update `goto_next`'s implementation to call `jump` with `float=true`.\r\n2. We should update the deprecated message to say \"Use |vim.diagnostic.jump()| with `{count = 1, float=true}` instead.\"\r\n\r\n### Neovim version (nvim -v)\r\n\r\nv0.11.0-3a8265\r\n\r\n### Language server name/version\r\n\r\nN/A\r\n\r\n### Operating system/version\r\n\r\nN/A\r\n\r\n### Log file\r\n\r\n_No response_",
